article.headline: Rutgers 60, Penn State 47
article.story: STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Ricky Shields and Quincy Douby each scored 17 points to lead Rutgers past Penn State 60-47 Wednesday night. The Scarlett Knights (4-1) opened up the second half with a 10-0 run to take a 44-26 lead. The Nittany Lions cut the lead to single digits but could never get closer than seven. Penn State (3-3) was led by DeForrest Riley-Smith's 20 points. The Lions were held to 28 percent shooting and were only 3-of-15 from 3-point range. Rutgers opened the game with a 12-2 run but Penn State came back to close the score to 12-10. The Scarlett Knights later went on a 13-5 first-half run, during which Douby hit three 3-pointers, to take a 32-20 lead. The Nittany Lions announced before the game that guard Brandon Cameron requested to be released so he could transfer schools. Cameron this season averaged 3.2 points and 2.6 rebounds in 17.4 minutes of playing time. Penn State forward Aaron Johnson played his first game of the season Wednesday after sitting out the first five following surgery to repair a detached retina. He scored four points.
